meta {
  name: Create User
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/users/manage
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "employeeName": "Anita Sharma",
    "username": "anita.sharma",
    "dateOfBirth": "1995-04-12",
    "gender": "FEMALE",
    "bloodGroup": "O_POS",
    "nationality": "Indian",
    "fatherName": "Ramesh Sharma",
    "motherName": "Sunita Sharma",
    "aadhaarNumber": "123456789012",
    "panNumber": "ABCDE1234F",
    "address": "12 MG Road, Bengaluru",
    "email": "anita.sharma@acme.test",
    "mobileNumber": "9812345678",
    "emergencyContactName": "Ramesh Sharma",
    "emergencyContactNumber": "9812300000",
    "password": "Str0ng@Pass1",
    "userType": "INTERNAL",
    "status": "ACTIVE",
    "branches": [
      { "branchId": "{{branchId}}", "roleKey": "lab_technician", "moduleId": "lab_operations", "isDefault": true, "branchStatus": "ACTIVE" }
    ]
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  branchId: b0b8fb9d-7c16-4cd1-b527-5c6cb12508a1
}

script:post-response {
  const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
  if (data) {
    if (data.person && data.person.id) bru.setEnvVar("manageUserId", data.person.id);
    if (data.userCode) bru.setEnvVar("manageUserCode", data.userCode);
    if (data.loginIdentifier) bru.setEnvVar("manageLoginIdentifier", data.loginIdentifier);
  }
}

docs {
  Create a staff user. Identity â†’ Person (Aadhaar encrypted), credentials â†’
  PersonCredentials (chosen `username` + `password`), employment â†’
  TenantStaffMembership (sequential `userCode`), branch assignment(s) â†’
  UserBranchProfile. Captures `manageUserId` and `manageUserCode`.
  
  Validation (all declarative): `employeeName`/parents = letters+spaces;
  `username` lowercase `[a-z0-9._]` (immutable); `dateOfBirth` â‰Ą 18 years;
  `aadhaarNumber` 12 digits; `panNumber` `AAAAA9999A`; `mobileNumber` Indian
  10-digit; `password` â‰Ą8 with upper/lower/digit/special; `userType`
  INTERNAL|EXTERNAL.
  
  Role model (v2.0):
  - The role is assigned **per branch** via `branches[].roleKey` (one role per
    branch). The top-level `roleKey` is an OPTIONAL primary/default role â€” omit it
    to create a user with no role and assign roles later (see "Register User
    (no role)" + "Assign Branches").
  - `branches[].moduleId` is the module linked to that assignment. It must be
    enabled for the branch (Branches â†’ Set Branch Modules) else 422
    MODULE_NOT_ENABLED_FOR_BRANCH; if the role template links specific modules, it
    must be one of them else 422 MODULE_NOT_IN_ROLE_TEMPLATE.
  - Each branch `roleKey` must be valid for that branch's type
    (PROFILE_BRANCH_MATRIX). Exactly one branch entry may be `isDefault: true`.
}
